dc_description_s: This data represents zoning for Waupaca County, Wisconsin in 2021, and includes the layers 'Waupaca_General_2021', and 'Waupaca_Shoreland_2021'. [General: Rural zoning districts for townships that fall under Waupaca County Zoning. Zoning data is tax parcel based. Shoreland: The hydrography coverage was created to represent rivers, water bodies and other hydrographic phenomena in Waupaca County. Hydrologic features were derived from the May 1994 flight with a flight height of 10,000 feet. The hydrologic feature layer is available in a county-wide or individual layer for each township, city, or village. The layer is based on the Waupaca County Coordinate System (WCCS).]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For access to the most current data for this county, please visit: [https://data2017-04-05t135915451z-waupacacounty.opendata.arcgis.com/][General: This file is rarely (if ever) fully representative of a dynamically changing landscape, the best that can be expected is data relative to a specific point in time.]
